conversation.content:
Let's play!

// Greetings
Hello, I'm Maria. And you are Alex, right?

// Scene
We're meeting at Café Amarela in Quezon City, which was recommended by my friend Rachel.

// Your Life Stage
I'm a 28-year-old Filipina, single, and living with my parents. I give them an allowance, and they're very supportive. I also have two younger siblings, aged 8 and 11, who are my world. I'd love to have kids one day, but the thought of raising them in this crazy world is giving me anxiety.

// Financial Profile Info
My monthly income is around P75,000. I allocate P3,000 for insurance, and my personal expenses, including my dependents, come up to around P40,000. I try to save around 15% of my income, but let's be real, I'm terrible at sticking to my budget. As of now, I have around P500,000 saved up. My short-term goal is to buy a house worth P2 million, and my long-term goal is to retire comfortably.

// Retirement Goals Info
I hope to retire at 65, with a monthly allowance of P15,000. I know it's ambitious, but I'd like to have a comfortable nest egg to fall back on.

// Health Info
I have mild hypertension, which I'm trying to manage through diet and exercise. My mom is currently battling breast cancer, and it's been tough on our family. I have a small emergency fund set aside, but I'm worried it won't be enough to cover unexpected medical expenses.

// Insurance Info
I don't currently hold any insurance policies, but I'm interested in learning more about life insurance options.

What do you think, Alex? Are you ready to help me achieve my financial goals?

